        <updateDate>2021-02-01T17:47:17Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Protecting Consumers from Market Manipulation Act</b></p> <p>This bill prohibits large nonfinancial companies from engaging in financial activities that would result in producing the lower of (1) 5% of the company's revenue, or (2) $1,000,000,000 in revenue. The bill limits the types of investment activities banks are allowed to engage in, including certain merchant banking activities. </p> <p>The Financial Stability Oversight Council and the Federal Reserve must report on issues related to digital currency. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
